<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-10T16:42:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-10T16:42:00-05:00" n="428" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/7349</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SJH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Shea</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-10T17:00:00-04:42">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 10, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your cipher telegram of October 9, 3 p.m., my cipher telegram May 28, 6
                            p.m., my despatch No. 134, May 29.<note n="1" xml:id="d428fn1">Despatch
                                not printed.</note> I have received memorandum from the Foreign
                            Office to the effect that merchant vessels armed for their own defense
                            will be treated in Chilean ports as merchant vessels provided their
                            Government previously notifies <pb facs="0534" n="1288" xml:id="pg_1288"/> Chilean Government of the name of the ship and provided that
                            itinerary, distribution, armament, absence of army or navy officers or
                            men, passenger list and merchandise make the ship appear to really be a
                            merchant vessel.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SJH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Shea</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>